Package: fontalign
Type: Package
Title: Backend-Agnostic Font Size Alignment for ggplot2 Outputs
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: person("fontalign contributors", email = "noreply@example.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Align rendered text size to a target DPI for plots produced by
    ggplot2, base graphics, or lattice, without modifying the original plot
    object or theme. Wraps ggsave() and routes complex-script text
    (Arabic, Persian, Devanagari, Thai) to a backend that supports HarfBuzz
    shaping (ragg or svglite). Targets Linux servers; on other platforms
    falls back gracefully.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
Depends: R (>= 4.0.0)
Imports:
    cli,
    grDevices,
    ggplot2,
    rlang,
    tools,
    utils
Suggests:
    testthat (>= 3.0.0),
    vdiffr,
    knitr,
    rmarkdown,
    ragg,
    svglite
RoxygenNote: 7.3.1
